Multiple trips to Israel have refined my Mediterranean palate and I’m so happy to find a place in my neighborhood that meets my standards! This is some of the most authentic Middle Eastern food in the city. I’ve tried almost everything on the menu and haven’t been disappointed yet. Somehow, each item has been better than the last. And they are all great. It’s in my regular rotation, which is saying something!

I work in the area and I was looking for a place like this, where I could eat healthy at a reasonable price. Also, they have a nice selection of drinks (non-alcoholic). I love this place not only for the high quality of the food (lamb is the best in my opinion) but also for the big windows and the light that the place has;  if you are not in a rush you can sit and look at the street and people passing by and just chill out a little bit.

I love this place! I have been looking for a good Schwarma place in nyc since I moved here and I finally found it. The place has variety of Israeli options (falafel, schwarma, kebab, etc). The pita they have is also amazing, which makes the whole difference. I have been there 3 times in the past few months and I wish I could go more often. Thank you for great food and amazing service!
